The spoken or written word, it is true, is only the symbol of the notion in the mind of the speaker or writer, but could the notion itself be formed or retained without the use of language? This or that particular word is, of course, separable from the corresponding idea (as is shewn by the mere fact of translation from one language into another), but, without the use of signs of some kind or other, we could hardly make any progress in thInking.
